page.title: 02ECOLOGY NETT'M & DISTRICT.
page.content: Habitat. Verges and hedges are cut or sprayed. Mature elms are dead. Playing fields,gardens,woodland at Sudbrooke, old orchards,Churchwood and Beck remain.Animals seen are:-moles,rabbits,voles,water and common shrews,rats,pipistrelle bats, hares,stoats,weasels,grey squirrels foxes and roe deer.Amphibia includes toads,frogs,pike,perch and roach. Dragon flies, damselflies,stoneflies and mayflies live in the Police Pond and Beck.Butterflies include large white,cabbagewhite,green veined white, orange tip,brimstone,copper,gatekeeper red admiral,tortoiseshell,peacock, comma.Birds include;owls,kestrels,rook red legged partridge,coots mallards, magpies swifts swallows martins,finch, wagtails,creepers, cuckoos,wrens, collared dove and titmice.The Watch meadow encourages wild flowers.
